quran[10]{c,v,t}:
  45,33,"And the evils they have wrought shall rise up into their view, and that at which they mocked shall hem them in on every side"
  45,34,"And it shall be said to them, \"This day will we forget you as ye forgat your meeting with us this day, and your abode shall be the fire, and none shall there be to succour you"
  45,35,"This, because ye received the signs of God with mockery, and this present life deceived you.\" On that day therefore they shall not come out from it; and they shall not be asked to win the favour of God"
  45,36,"Praise then be to God, Lord of the Heavens and Lord of the Earth; the Lord of the worlds"
  45,37,"And His be the greatness in the Heavens and on the Earth; for He is the Mighty, the Wise"
  46,1,HA. MIM
  46,2,"The Revelation (sending down) of this Book is from the Mighty, the Wise"
  46,3,"We have not created the Heavens and the Earth and all that is between them otherwise than in truth and for a settled term. But they who believe not, turn away from their warning"
  46,4,"SAY: What think ye? As for those whom ye invoke beside God, shew me what part of the earth it is which they have created? Had they a share in the Heavens? Bring me a Book sent down by them before this Koran, or traces of their knowledge; - if ye are men of truth"
  46,5,"And who erreth more than he who, beside God, calleth upon that which shall not answer him until the day of Resurrection? Yes, they regard not their invocations"